sysGenInfoCustomerName.name: sysGenInfoCustomerName
sysGenInfoCustomerName.description: Name of the organization that uses the managed node.

sysGenInfoPhoneNumber.name: sysGenInfoPhoneNumber
sysGenInfoPhoneNumber.description: Phone number of the organization that uses the managed node.

sysGenInfoMaintenanceContact.name: sysGenInfoMaintenanceContact
sysGenInfoMaintenanceContact.description: Maintenance contact of the managed node.

sysGenInfoAutoLogoutTime.name: sysGenInfoAutoLogoutTime
sysGenInfoAutoLogoutTime.description: The time a TELNET or VT-100 terminal user can maintain a session with the managed node without any keyboard action. Unit: minute

sysGenInfoPassword.name: sysGenInfoPassword
sysGenInfoPassword.description: Password required to access the managed node using VT-100 terminal or TELNET. A get request always returns a NULL string.

sysGenInfoShelfId.name: sysGenInfoShelfId
sysGenInfoShelfId.description: LX-10 unit identification number required to identify and set up the device's role (primary/secondary). This number should be unique among interconnected devices.

sysTimeAndDate.name: sysTimeAndDate
sysTimeAndDate.description: Time and date maintained in the managed node.

sysIpConfigHostInterfaceTable.name: sysIpConfigHostInterfaceTable
sysIpConfigHostInterfaceTable.description: Table of available host IP interfaces.

sysIpConfigHostInterfaceEntry.name: sysIpConfigHostInterfaceEntry
sysIpConfigHostInterfaceEntry.description: Each entry contains the IP address and subnet mask of the specified interface and a flag which enables/disables the managed node to broadcast its (RIP) routing table through the interface.

sysIpConfigHostInterfaceXmtRoutingMsg.name: sysIpConfigHostInterfaceXmtRoutingMsg
sysIpConfigHostInterfaceXmtRoutingMsg.description: This object controls whether the managed node should broadcast its (RIP) routing table through the interface.

sysIpConfigTrapClientEntry.name: sysIpConfigTrapClientEntry
sysIpConfigTrapClientEntry.description: Each entry contains IP address and port number of an SNMP manager which receives traps from the managed node.

sysIpConfigCommunityName.name: sysIpConfigCommunityName
sysIpConfigCommunityName.description: Community name of the managed node. A get request for an instance of this object always returns a NULL string.

sysIpConfigMacAddress.name: sysIpConfigMacAddress
sysIpConfigMacAddress.description: MAC-layer address of the management Ethernet port.

sysRs232Table.name: sysRs232Table
sysRs232Table.description: This table contains 2 rows. The first row shows the physical configuration of the port connected to a VT100 termianl. The second row is used to configure the port which supports SLIP. Access to the first row is read-only and access to the second row is read-write.

sysRs232Entry.name: sysRs232Entry
sysRs232Entry.description: Each entry contains the attributes of a serial port.

sysRs232Port.name: sysRs232Port
sysRs232Port.description: The managed node has 2 serial ports: port 1 and port 2.

sysRs232BaudRate.name: sysRs232BaudRate
sysRs232BaudRate.description: Baud rate. The instance of this object in port-1 is read-only.

sysRs232Parity.name: sysRs232Parity
sysRs232Parity.description: Parity. The instance of this object in port-1 is read-only.

sysRs232DataBits.name: sysRs232DataBits
sysRs232DataBits.description: Number of data bits. The instance of this object in port-1 is read-only.

sysRs232StopBits.name: sysRs232StopBits
sysRs232StopBits.description: Number of stop bits. The instance of this object in port-1 is read-only.

sysMainProcessorFirmwareRev.name: sysMainProcessorFirmwareRev
sysMainProcessorFirmwareRev.description: Firmware revision of the management CPU.

sysPortCardFirmwareRev.name: sysPortCardFirmwareRev
sysPortCardFirmwareRev.description: Firmware revision of the Ethernet (DATA) card.

configDs1Entry.name: configDs1Entry
configDs1Entry.description: Each entry contains the configuration attributes for a DS1 port.

configDs1LBO.name: configDs1LBO
configDs1LBO.description: LBO. This object is not accessible if the managed node is the E1 version of LX10.

configDs1Encoding.name: configDs1Encoding
configDs1Encoding.description: Encoding. This object is not accessible if the managed node is the E1 version of LX10.

configDs1Framing.name: configDs1Framing
configDs1Framing.description: Framing format. This object is not accessible if the managed node is the E1 version of LX10.

configAfaActivationRate.name: configAfaActivationRate
configAfaActivationRate.description: AFA activation rate is used by the managed node to decide when it will disable the operational status of a T1 interface if the interface's BER rate is above the selected activation rate for a period specified by configAfaActivationTime (see below).

configAfaDeactivationRate.name: configAfaDeactivationRate
configAfaDeactivationRate.description: AFA deactivation rate is used by the managed node to decide when it will enable the operational status of a T1 interface if the interface's BER rate is below the selected activation rate for a period specified by configAfaDectivationTime (see below).

configAfaFarEndLpbkDetect.name: configAfaFarEndLpbkDetect
configAfaFarEndLpbkDetect.description: This object controls whether AFA will be activated when a near end LX-10 detects network loopback in the far end LX-10. If it's disabled, no AFA will be activated because of a far end network loopback.

configPortCardType.name: configPortCardType
configPortCardType.description: There are 3 kinds of cards/port supported by the managed node: HSDP, Ethernet, or Token-Ring. Only one of them can be installed in the managed node. Hsdp is a high speed data port with v.35, rs-422, and HSSI interfaces.

configHsdpCtsControl.name: configHsdpCtsControl
configHsdpCtsControl.description: CTS line control in HSDP. If the value of an instance of this object is set, the CTS line will always be set. If the value of an instance of this object is no-bandwidth, the CTS line will go low when no bandwidth is available after a hold-off time. If the value of an instance of this object is frequency- change, the CTS line will go low for a hold-off time when there is a frequency change.

configHsdpCtsStatus.name: configHsdpCtsStatus
configHsdpCtsStatus.description: Status of CTS line in HSDP.

configHsdpTermTimingSource.name: configHsdpTermTimingSource
configHsdpTermTimingSource.description: Terminal timing source in HSDP. It applies only when the value of the instance of configHsdpMode is v-35 or rs-422.

configHsdpTermTiming.name: configHsdpTermTiming
configHsdpTermTiming.description: Status of terminal timing in HSDP. It applies only when the value of the instance of configHsdpMode is v-35 or rs-422.

configHsdpRecvTiming.name: configHsdpRecvTiming
configHsdpRecvTiming.description: Status of receive timing in HSDP. It applies only when the value of the instance of configHsdpMode is v-35 or rs-422.

configHsdpHoldoffSeconds.name: configHsdpHoldoffSeconds
configHsdpHoldoffSeconds.description: Hold-off time for CA lead. If the hold-off is set at 5 seconds, and if the CTS control is sensitive to no-bandwidth, the CTS line will go low after 5 seconds when no bandwidth is available. If the CTS control is sensitive to frequency-change, the CTS line will stay low for 5 seconds when there is a frequency change, and then back to high.

configHdlcMode.name: configHdlcMode
configHdlcMode.description: Select the way in which HDLC port will be assigned. If mode is manual, the HDLC port is selectable by the NMS. If mode is auto, the 2 LX-10's in the 2 sides will match their HDLC ports automatically.

configHdlcLocalPort.name: configHdlcLocalPort
configHdlcLocalPort.description: Assign one of the DS1 ports as the HDLC port. If its value is 0, no port is asssigned as the HDLC port.

configHdlcFarEndPort.name: configHdlcFarEndPort
configHdlcFarEndPort.description: The DS1 port currently being used as the HDLC port in the far end LX-10.

configInverseMux.name: configInverseMux
configInverseMux.description: Master/slave relationship of the 2 LX-10E's in the point to point connection.

faultDs1LoopbackTable.name: faultDs1LoopbackTable
faultDs1LoopbackTable.description: DS1 loopback table for 7 DS1 ports.

faultDs1LoopbackEntry.name: faultDs1LoopbackEntry
faultDs1LoopbackEntry.description: Each entry in the table contains the loopback status of a DS1 port.

faultDs1LoopbackPort.name: faultDs1LoopbackPort
faultDs1LoopbackPort.description: The port number of one of the 7 DS1 ports

faultDs1LoopbackNetworkLoopback.name: faultDs1LoopbackNetworkLoopback
faultDs1LoopbackNetworkLoopback.description: DS1 loopback is used to control the loopback state of one of the 7 DS1 interfaces in the managed node.

faultDs1RemoteLineLoopback.name: faultDs1RemoteLineLoopback
faultDs1RemoteLineLoopback.description: This loopback status is controlled by the LA/LB leads in the remote node.

faultDteLaLead.name: faultDteLaLead
faultDteLaLead.description: The state of the LA loopbak lead.

faultDteLbLead.name: faultDteLbLead
faultDteLbLead.description: The state of the LB loopbak lead.

faultDteLaLbTranslation.name: faultDteLaLbTranslation
faultDteLaLbTranslation.description: The managed node uses the states of the LA and LB leads to decide what kind of loopback to perform if faultLaLbLoopbackEnable (see below) is ENABLED. The meaning of LA and LB leads is as follows: loopback LA-Lead LB-Lead ------------------------------------------------ none clear clear local-line set clear remote-line clear set dte set set

faultDteLaLbLoopbackEnable.name: faultDteLaLbLoopbackEnable
faultDteLaLbLoopbackEnable.description: Enable/disable the managed node to use the LA and LB lead states to perform loopbaks.

faultDteCustomerLoopback.name: faultDteCustomerLoopback
faultDteCustomerLoopback.description: Enable/disable the customer equipment (DTE) to perform loopback toward the managed node.

faultDteDteLoopback.name: faultDteDteLoopback
faultDteDteLoopback.description: Enable/disable the managed node to perform loopback toward the customer equipment (DTE).

faultClearCurrentAlarms.name: faultClearCurrentAlarms
faultClearCurrentAlarms.description: A set request clears all entries in the current alarm table. A get/get-next request returns 0.

faultClearHistoryAlarms.name: faultClearHistoryAlarms
faultClearHistoryAlarms.description: A set request clears all entries in the history alarm table. A get/get-next request returns 0.

faultCurrentAlarmEntry.name: faultCurrentAlarmEntry
faultCurrentAlarmEntry.description: Each entry in the table contains the information of a currently active alarm.

faultCurrentAlarmTag.name: faultCurrentAlarmTag
faultCurrentAlarmTag.description: The tag of the alarm in the current alarm table.

faultCurrentAlarmAlarmType.name: faultCurrentAlarmAlarmType
faultCurrentAlarmAlarmType.description: The alarm type of the alarm.

faultCurrentAlarmCardType.name: faultCurrentAlarmCardType
faultCurrentAlarmCardType.description: The type of the card which caused the alarm.

faultCurrentAlarmPortNumber.name: faultCurrentAlarmPortNumber
faultCurrentAlarmPortNumber.description: The port number of the card which caused the alarm. Its value is between 1 and 7 for DS1 ports and 0 for others.

faultCurrentAlarmSetTime.name: faultCurrentAlarmSetTime
faultCurrentAlarmSetTime.description: The time when the alarm was set.

faultCurrentAlarmDescription.name: faultCurrentAlarmDescription
faultCurrentAlarmDescription.description: A readable string which describes the alarm. Its format is as follows: <Level> <Card> <Port> <Alarm Type> <Time Occured> 'Level' is the alarm severity. Its value can be 'Info', 'Major', or 'Minor'. 'Card' refers to where the alarm was generated. Its value can be 'HSDP', 'ENET', 'TRING', or 'DS1'. 'Port' refers to which port generated the alarm. Its value can be 1 to 7 for DS1 and 'empty' if no port number can be used for an alarm. 'Alarm Type' is an ASCII string of the alarm type. 'Time Occured' is the time when the alarm was generated.

faultHistoryAlarmEntry.name: faultHistoryAlarmEntry
faultHistoryAlarmEntry.description: Each entry in the history alarm table contains either a cleared alarm or an information alarm.

faultHistoryAlarmTag.name: faultHistoryAlarmTag
faultHistoryAlarmTag.description: The tag of the alarm in the history alarm table.

faultHistoryAlarmAlarmType.name: faultHistoryAlarmAlarmType
faultHistoryAlarmAlarmType.description: The alarm type of the alarm.

faultHistoryAlarmSeverity.name: faultHistoryAlarmSeverity
faultHistoryAlarmSeverity.description: The severity of the alarm. Its value can be either major or minor for DS1 ports and info for others.

faultHistoryAlarmCardType.name: faultHistoryAlarmCardType
faultHistoryAlarmCardType.description: The type of the card which caused the alarm.

faultHistoryAlarmPortNumber.name: faultHistoryAlarmPortNumber
faultHistoryAlarmPortNumber.description: The port number of the card which caused the alarm. Its value is between 1 and 7 for DS1 ports and 0 for others.

faultHistoryAlarmSetTime.name: faultHistoryAlarmSetTime
faultHistoryAlarmSetTime.description: The time when the alarm was set.

faultHistoryAlarmClearTime.name: faultHistoryAlarmClearTime
faultHistoryAlarmClearTime.description: The time when the alarm was cleared.

faultHistoryAlarmDescription.name: faultHistoryAlarmDescription
faultHistoryAlarmDescription.description: A readable string which describes the alarm. Its format is as follows: <Level> <Card> <Port> <Alarm Type> <Time Occured> <Time Cleared> 'Level' is the alarm severity. Its value can be 'Info', 'Major', or 'Minor'. 'Card' refers to where the alarm was generated. Its value can be 'HSDP', 'ENET', 'TRING', or 'DS1'. 'Port' refers to which port generated the alarm. Its value can be 1 to 7 for DS1 and 'empty' if no port number can be used for an alarm. 'Alarm Type' is an ASCII string of the alarm type. 'Time Occured' is the time when the alarm was generated. 'Time Cleared' is the time when the alarm was cleared.

perfClearDs1Performance.name: perfClearDs1Performance
perfClearDs1Performance.description: A set request clears all DS1 performance monitoring data. A get/get-next request returns 0.

perfClearEnetPortCardStats.name: perfClearEnetPortCardStats
perfClearEnetPortCardStats.description: A set request clears all ethernet port card statistics. A get/get-next request returns 0.

enetPortCardStatsFramesReceived.name: enetPortCardStatsFramesReceived
enetPortCardStatsFramesReceived.description: A count of frames received by the ethernet port card.

enetPortCardStatsBytesReceived.name: enetPortCardStatsBytesReceived
enetPortCardStatsBytesReceived.description: A count of bytes received by the ethernet port card.

enetPortCardStatsFramesTransmitted.name: enetPortCardStatsFramesTransmitted
enetPortCardStatsFramesTransmitted.description: A count of frames transmitted on the ethernet port card.

enetPortCardStatsBytesTransmitted.name: enetPortCardStatsBytesTransmitted
enetPortCardStatsBytesTransmitted.description: A count of bytes transmitted on the ethernet port card.

enetPortCardStatsAlignmentErrors.name: enetPortCardStatsAlignmentErrors
enetPortCardStatsAlignmentErrors.description: A count of frames received that are not an integral number of octets in length and do not pass the FCS check. The count represented by an instance of this object is incremented when the alignmentError status is returned by the MAC service to the LLC (or other MAC user). Received frames for which multiple error conditions obtain are, according to the conventions of IEEE 802.3 Layer Management, counted exclusively according to the error status presented to the LLC.

enetPortCardStatsFCSErrors.name: enetPortCardStatsFCSErrors
enetPortCardStatsFCSErrors.description: A count of frames received that are an integral number of octets in length but do not pass the FCS check. The count represented by an instance of this object is incremented when the frameCheckError status is returned by the MAC service to the LLC (or other MAC user). Received frames for which multiple error conditions obtain are, according to the conventions of IEEE 802.3 Layer Management, counted exclusively according to the error status presented to the LLC.

enetPortCardStatsSingleCollisionFrames.name: enetPortCardStatsSingleCollisionFrames
enetPortCardStatsSingleCollisionFrames.description: A count of successfully transmitted frames for which transmission is inhibited by exactly one collision. A frame that is counted by an instance of this object is not counted by the corresponding instance of the enetPortCardStatsMultipleCollisionFrames object.

enetPortCardStatsMultipleCollisionFrames.name: enetPortCardStatsMultipleCollisionFrames
enetPortCardStatsMultipleCollisionFrames.description: A count of successfully transmitted frames for which transmission is inhibited by more than one collision. A frame that is counted by an instance of this object is not counted by the corresponding instance of the enetPortCardStatsSingleCollisionFrames object.

enetPortCardStatsDeferredTransmissions.name: enetPortCardStatsDeferredTransmissions
enetPortCardStatsDeferredTransmissions.description: A count of frames for which the first transmission attempt is delayed because the medium is busy. The count represented by an instance of this object does not include frames involved in collisions.

enetPortCardStatsLateCollisions.name: enetPortCardStatsLateCollisions
enetPortCardStatsLateCollisions.description: The number of times that a collision is detected on later than 512 bit-times into the transmission of a packet. Five hundred and twelve bit-times corresponds to 51.2 microseconds on a 10 Mbit/s system. A (late) collision included in a count represented by an instance of this object is also considered as a (generic) collision for purposes of other collision-related statistics.

enetPortCardStatsExcessiveCollisions.name: enetPortCardStatsExcessiveCollisions
enetPortCardStatsExcessiveCollisions.description: A count of frames for which transmission fails due to excessive collisions.

enetPortCardStatsInternalMacTransmitErro.name: enetPortCardStatsInternalMacTransmitErrors
enetPortCardStatsInternalMacTransmitErro.description: A count of frames for which transmission fails due to an internal MAC sublayer transmit error. A frame is only counted by an instance of this object if it is not counted by the corresponding instance of either the enetPortCardStatsLateCollisions object, the enetPortCardStatsExcessiveCollisions object, or the enetPortCardStatsCarrierSenseErrors object. The precise meaning of the count represented by an instance of this object is implementation- specific. In particular, an instance of this object may represent a count of transmission errors that are not otherwise counted.

enetPortCardStatsCarrierSenseErrors.name: enetPortCardStatsCarrierSenseErrors
enetPortCardStatsCarrierSenseErrors.description: The number of times that the carrier sense condition was lost or never asserted when attempting to transmit a frame. The count represented by an instance of this object is incremented at most once per transmission attempt, even if the carrier sense condition fluctuates during a transmission attempt.

enetPortCardStatsFrameTooLongs.name: enetPortCardStatsFrameTooLongs
enetPortCardStatsFrameTooLongs.description: A count of frames received that exceed the maximum permitted frame size. The count represented by an instance of this object is incremented when the frameTooLong status is returned by the MAC service to the LLC (or other MAC user). Received frames for which multiple error conditions obtain are, according to the conventions of IEEE 802.3 Layer Management, counted exclusively according to the error status presented to the LLC.

perfClearNxT1PortStats.name: perfClearNxT1PortStats
perfClearNxT1PortStats.description: A set request clears all nxt1 port statistics. A get/get-next request returns 0.

nxt1PortStatsFramesReceived.name: nxt1PortStatsFramesReceived
nxt1PortStatsFramesReceived.description: A count of frames received by the NxT1 port.

nxt1PortStatsBytesReceived.name: nxt1PortStatsBytesReceived
nxt1PortStatsBytesReceived.description: A count of bytes received by the NxT1 port.

nxt1PortStatsFramesTransmitted.name: nxt1PortStatsFramesTransmitted
nxt1PortStatsFramesTransmitted.description: A count of frames transmitted on the NxT1 port.

nxt1PortStatsBytesTransmitted.name: nxt1PortStatsBytesTransmitted
nxt1PortStatsBytesTransmitted.description: A count of bytes transmitted on the NxT1 port.

nxt1PortStatsCrcErrors.name: nxt1PortStatsCrcErrors
nxt1PortStatsCrcErrors.description: A count of frames received by the NxT1 port that do not pass the CRC check.

alarmOnReport.name: alarmOnReport
alarmOnReport.description: LX-10-specific trap sent by the managed node when an alarm condition is set.

alarmOffReport.name: alarmOffReport
alarmOffReport.description: LX-10-specific trap sent by the managed node when an alarm condition is cleared.
